<br>
Blizzard has made good games as well, no doubt about it. While I personally think that WC was a Dune II clone in a Warhammer world, its fairly obvious that a lot of people liked the series. Blizzard games tend to be released with very few bugs. On the other hand, the D2 BNet servercode was so unstable that you might have suspected that they had outsourced the development to Funcom. While Blizzard tend to release bugfree games they also tend to be outdated by the time they are released. In the RTS genre this might not mean much, but I think this could be a disadvantage for a MMORPG. The WC3 engine for example is workable, but its outdated even today. While I don't mind the WoW graphics I'm not sure how well they stand up to the competition in a year or two.<br>
<br>
That being said, I probably will try both EQ2 and WoW. My greatest concern with both games is that they might lack in complexity because the companies think that will sell more copies. Also, listening too much to customers is a bad thing. Lets hope they don't make that misstake.<br>
